{{Orphan|date=March 2017}}

In Hungary, a '''dohánybolt''', in full '''nemzeti dohánybolt''' ({{ety|hu|nemzeti|national||dohány|tobacco||bolt|shop, store}}) is a government-approved and government-controlled shop that sells [[tobacco]] products.

The shops must not have wares on display to those outside, similar to the rules for [[betting shop]]s in the United Kingdom. Depending on the size of the shop, they also may often serve coffee and [[soft drink]]s, but it is illegal to smoke in a dohánybolt. Some of the larger have tables outside and essentially become a [[café]].

