{{Infobox disease | Name = Lactation failure | Image = | Caption = | DiseasesDB = | ICD10 = {{ICD10|O|92|3|o|85}} | ICD9 = {{ICD9|676.4}} | ICDO = | OMIM = | MedlinePlus = | eMedicineSubj = | eMedicineTopic = | MeshID = }}
In [[breastfeeding]], '''lactation failure''' may refer to: * '''Primary lactation failure''', a cause of [[low milk supply]] in breastfeeding mothers * Cessation of breastfeeding before the mother had planned to stop, usually as a result of [[breastfeeding difficulties]] * [[Low milk supply]] in general
Lactation failure can result in [[neonatal jaundice]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://medlineplus.gov/ency/article/000995.htm|title=Jaundice and breastfeeding: MedlinePlus Medical Encyclopedia|website=medlineplus.gov|language=en|access-date=2018-11-07}}</ref>
